{
  "texts": [
    "Duties of attention arguably obtain in less intimate relationships as well, such as the relationship between fellow citizens of a democratic polity.",
    "On January 6th 2021, US Americans plausibly owed it to each other to pay appropriate attention to the insurrection at the Capitol.",
    "If so, then those who indifferently scrolled past the headlines failed in their civic duties of attention, as did those who closely followed the developments with glee, hoping that the election results wouldn't be certified.",
    "Again, judicious attention allocation matters in such cases in part because of its effects on actions and outcomes.",
    "But it also matters in its own right."
  ]
}